    <p style="font-size:.78rem;color:var(--light);margin-top:.8rem">Secure payment · automatic tax receipt (FR) · helloasso.com</p>

    <!-- ── INFOGRAPHIE 100€ — VRAIS CHIFFRES BILAN 2025 ── -->
    <div class="infograph">
      <div class="infograph-title">Where does your donation go?</div>
      <div class="infograph-sub">2025 audit — for every €100 you give</div>
      <div class="infograph-bar" role="img" aria-label="Allocation of €100: €91.80 social missions, €0 fundraising, €8.20 operations">
        <div class="infograph-seg infograph-seg-1"><div class="pct">€91.80</div></div>
        <div class="infograph-seg infograph-seg-2"></div>
        <div class="infograph-seg infograph-seg-3"><div class="pct">€8.20</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="infograph-legend" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr">
        <div class="infograph-leg"><div class="dot c1"></div><div><strong>€91.80</strong>directly forwarded to field NGOs (orphanages, schools, disability support, emergencies)</div></div>
        <div class="infograph-leg"><div class="dot c3"></div><div><strong>€8.20</strong>covers field-monitoring travel and banking fees</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="infograph-note"><strong style="color:var(--brown);font-family:'Inter',sans-serif">€0</strong> in fundraising costs — Rejoice spends nothing on marketing or fundraising.<br>2025 accounts presented by OnlyCompta · Séverine GOUJET, certified accountant · April 7, 2026.<br><em>Accounts presentation — not a full audit (appropriate for our size).</em></div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── FAQ ACCORDEON ── -->
    <div class="faq" id="faq">
      <div class="faq-head">
        <p class="s-label" style="text-align:center">Your questions</p>
        <h3>Everything we get asked</h3>
        <p>Click to open an answer — and write to us if yours isn't here.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Is my donation really used on the ground?</span>
          <span class="faq-q-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">
          <p>Yes. Laurent Perraud, president of Rejoice, personally goes to the field several times a year (India, Nepal, projects in France) to ensure funds are properly used and to maintain direct relationships with partner organizations.</p>
          <p>Our principle: <strong>no opaque intermediaries, direct ties with the local NGOs</strong> we support — B.I.A. orphanage in Nepal, K.C.E. school in India, etc.</p>
        </div></div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How much does Rejoice keep for operations?</span>
          <span class="faq-q-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">
          <p>Rejoice is a young French non-profit (created in 2024). For fiscal year 2025, <strong>91.8% of expenses</strong> went directly to field NGOs as financial aid (€20,000 out of €21,795 total). The <strong>remaining 8.2%</strong> covers Laurent's field-monitoring travel and banking fees.</p>
          <p>Rejoice operates <strong>without any salary, without marketing costs, without fundraising costs</strong>. The structure is deliberately lean to maximize what reaches the ground.</p>
          <p>The non-profit built a reserve over 2024–2025: agreements with our field partners (NGOs in India and Nepal) took time to finalize. <strong>These agreements are now in place</strong> and significant amounts are currently being forwarded for the 2026 fiscal year.</p>
          <p>The 2025 accounts were presented by OnlyCompta (Séverine GOUJET, certified accountant). This is an <em>accounts presentation</em>, the appropriate engagement for our size, not a full audit. <a href="bilan-2025.pdf" download>Download the 2025 financial report (PDF, in French) →</a></p>
        </div></div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How does the tax deduction work exactly?</span>
          <span class="faq-q-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">
          <p><strong>Important — applies to French taxpayers only</strong></p>
          <p>The tax benefits described below apply to taxpayers in France. If you live abroad, please check your local tax rules — most countries do not recognize foreign charitable donations for tax deduction.</p><p><strong>For individuals (French residents):</strong> as a French non-profit of general interest (loi 1901), donations to Rejoice qualify for:</p>
          <p><strong>66% income tax reduction</strong> (capped at 20% of taxable income). Concretely: if you donate €100, you get €66 back on your taxes — the donation only costs you €34.</p>
          <p><strong>75% IFI tax reduction</strong> if you pay French Property Wealth Tax (capped at €50,000 in reduction). €100 donated = €25 net cost.</p>
          <p style="margin-top:1.2rem"><strong>For companies (corporate sponsorship — art. 238 bis of the French Tax Code)</strong></p>
          <p>French companies receive a <strong>60% tax reduction</strong> on the donation amount, capped at <strong>€20,000 OR 0.5% of pre-tax turnover</strong> — whichever is more advantageous.</p>
          <p>Concretely: a €1,000 donation only costs the company €400 after the reduction. For SMEs, the 0.5% turnover cap often goes well beyond €20,000. Above the cap, the excess can be <strong>carried over to the next 5 fiscal years</strong>.</p>
          <p style="margin-top:1.2rem">The tax receipt is generated <strong>automatically by HelloAsso</strong> with each donation and sent to your email (only useful for French taxpayers).</p>
        </div></div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Can I donate monthly rather than one-off?</span>
          <span class="faq-q-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">
          <p>Yes — and it's actually our preferred option: a monthly donation, even modest, lets us plan our field commitments over time. HelloAsso offers this option directly in the donation form, and you can stop it at any time.</p>
          <p>€10/month = €120/year = <strong>€40.80 net after the FR tax reduction</strong>.</p>
        </div></div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What if I want to support a specific project?</span>
          <span class="faq-q-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">
          <p>It's possible: you can specify in the message field when donating via HelloAsso (or by email to <a href="mailto:contact@rejoice.ngo">contact@rejoice.ngo</a>) the project you care most about — B.I.A. orphanage Nepal, K.C.E. school India, emergency aid…</p>
          <p>We channel those donations to the designated project and keep you informed in our next reports.</p>
        </div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

